# API Endpoint Documentation Rule

When adding new API endpoints to this project, **always create or update a Postman collection file**.

## Requirements

1. **Create a `.postman_collection.json` file** in the project root with all new endpoints
2. **Include for each endpoint:**
   - Method (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
   - Full URL with `{{baseUrl}}` variable
   - Headers (Content-Type: application/json for POST/PUT)
   - Example request body for POST/PUT requests
   - Query parameters for GET requests

## File Naming

- Use descriptive names: `{feature}-endpoints.postman_collection.json`
- Examples: `customer-location-ratings.postman_collection.json`, `billing-endpoints.postman_collection.json`

## Postman Collection Format

```json
{
    "info": {
        "name": "Feature Name - Endpoints",
        "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
    },
    "variable": [
        {"key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:8000"}
    ],
    "item": [
        {
            "name": "Endpoint Name",
            "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "url": "{{baseUrl}}/api/endpoint",
                "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}],
                "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"field\": \"value\"}"}
            }
        }
    ]
}
```

## After Adding Endpoints

1. Create/update the Postman collection file
2. Inform the user they can import it via: **Postman → Import → Upload Files**
